Mainova AG (FWB: MNV6) is one of the largest regional energy suppliers in Germany and supplies about one million people in Hesse and neighboring provinces with electricity, gas, heat and water. It is based in Frankfurt am Main. Mainova AG was formed in 1998 through the merger of Stadtwerke Frankfurt am Main GmbH and Maingas AG. The energy and water utility has approximately 2,900 employees and posted 2009 sales of 1.66 billion. The largest shareholder of Mainova are the government of Frankfurt am Main with a 75.2% ownership stake of shares and Thga AG with 24.4% of the shares. The remaining shares (0.4%) are freely floated. The board members are Dr. Constantin Alsheimer (CEO), Dr. Marie-Luise Wolff, Dr. Peter Birkner and Lothar Herbst. The Chairman of Mainova is Frankfurt mayor Petra Roth. 
